::Spears::

She felt the pod shake again.  She held onto the she chair next to 
her with a death grip. Her nuckles were white. She had her eyes 
closed and gritting her teeth. She spoke in a quiet but painicked 
voice. "Please...just ...get ..me ..out...of..this ..pod..please."
She was almost begging him.  She just had to get her feet back onto 
firm ground.  She was a warrior, one who feared nothing, except for 
heights and flying.  She felt about an inch tall with this whole 
situations.  She felt totally helpless while in the pod and hated 
feeling like that.  Heights was her one and only weakness.  She was 
just glad that Striker was on her side now that he knew about her 
acraphobia.
